OL,3,CPolice officer cleared of strangling
OL,4,Cgirl, 16, while she was handcuffed
OL,6,FThe girl later claimed she had been
OL,7,Fstrangled. PC Markowski testified that
OL,8,Fhe removed his hands after the girl
OL,9,Fcomplained of being choked.
OL,11,FThe investigation, which lasted four
OL,12,Fmonths, concluded with a file of
OL,13,Fevidence being sent to the Crown
OL,14,FProsecution Service (CPS).
OL,16,FThe CPS subsequently decided to press
OL,17,Fcharges against the officer.
OL,18,FInitially, PC Markowski also faced a
OL,19,Fcharge of assault by beating, which
OL,20,Fwas withdrawn at the start of the
OL,21,Ftrial.
